hell.definition:
1) any place of pain and turmoil;
2) a cause of difficulty and suffering
3) (Christianity) the abode of Satan and the forces of evil; where sinners suffer eternal punishment

horn.definition:
1) stab or pierce with a horn or tusk
2) one of the bony outgrowths on the heads of certain ungulates
3) a noise made by the driver of an automobile to give warning;
